        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 2:02AM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 201 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Van Wyck to 8 miles east of Pageland.
Movement was southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and periods of heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.  Heavy rain could cause minor flooding.

Locations impacted include...
Lancaster, Indian Land, Waxhaw, Pageland, Chesterfield, Andrew
Jackson State Park, USC Lancaster, Van Wyck, Buford, Jefferson, Ruby,
Mount Croghan, Chesterfield Ruby Middle School, High Point Fire
Station, Arrowood Estates, Tradesville, Camp Creek Fire Station,
Antioch, Forty Acre Rock Preserve, and Taxahaw.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
